If you haven't been with us before,

17
00:00:54,131 --> 00:00:55,680
hang around.

18
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,491
I think you'll really
enjoy what we're gonna do.

19
00:00:57,491 --> 00:00:59,271
I've already covered the canvas

20
00:00:59,271 --> 00:01:01,051
with a thin, even coat of Magic White.

21
00:01:01,051 --> 00:01:02,771
And the Magic White, it makes the canvas

22
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,251
wet, makes it slick.

23
00:01:04,251 --> 00:01:07,370
It allows us to literally blend
color right on the canvas.

24
00:01:07,370 --> 00:01:09,470
So, let's go up here and do it.

25
00:01:09,471 --> 00:01:10,912
And I'll start with a big old

26
00:01:10,912 --> 00:01:12,151
two and a half inch brush today.

27
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:14,450
And we'll go right into a
little bit of thalo blue.

28
00:01:14,450 --> 00:01:15,971
And we'll just work some of that

29
00:01:15,971 --> 00:01:17,230
right into the bristles here.

30
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:19,271
Just beat it into the bristles,

31
00:01:19,271 --> 00:01:21,210
so you have a nice, even
distribution of color.

32
00:01:21,210 --> 00:01:23,170
(thumping)

33
00:01:23,171 --> 00:01:24,722
Kay, let's go up to the canvas here.

34
00:01:24,721 --> 00:01:26,141
Maybe we'll make a, let's just make a

35
00:01:26,141 --> 00:01:27,322
happy little sky here.

36
00:01:27,322 --> 00:01:29,192
We just use a little,
little criss-cross strokes.

37
00:01:29,191 --> 00:01:30,922
(brushing)

38
00:01:30,923 --> 00:01:33,162
And just let the brush
just sort of bounce around

39
00:01:33,162 --> 00:01:34,121
and play and

40
00:01:34,121 --> 00:01:35,522
just let it have fun.

41
00:01:36,822 --> 00:01:38,152
Let it have fun.

42
00:01:38,941 --> 00:01:40,151
A little more color.

43
00:01:40,152 --> 00:01:41,701
And we'll go up here in this corner.

44
00:01:41,701 --> 00:01:42,661
(brushing)

45
00:01:42,662 --> 00:01:44,532
And I'm not coloring the
entire canvas evenly.

46
00:01:44,531 --> 00:01:46,272
I'm leaving some little
spots here and there that

47
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:48,182
oh, hopefully when we're
done it'll look like

48
00:01:48,182 --> 00:01:50,822
some happy little clouds
floating all across the sky.

49
00:01:52,652 --> 00:01:53,671
There.

50
00:01:54,522 --> 00:01:55,792
(thumping)

51
00:01:55,792 --> 00:01:57,781
Now, it's easy, it's real
easy to make the sky darker.

52
00:01:57,781 --> 00:01:59,682
But, it's a son of a
gun to make it lighter.

53
00:01:59,682 --> 00:02:01,972
(scraping)

54
00:02:01,981 --> 00:02:04,762
So, use very, very little
color when you first start.

55
00:02:04,762 --> 00:02:06,382
You can always go back and add more color.

56
00:02:08,051 --> 00:02:10,341
Now, while I've got this
old dirty brush going here,

57
00:02:10,342 --> 00:02:12,562
I'm gonna reach right up into this color,

58
00:02:12,562 --> 00:02:14,201
which is a little bit of thalo green.

59
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:16,481
And we want very, very small amounts.

60
00:02:16,481 --> 00:02:18,562
Extremely, extremely strong.

61
00:02:19,812 --> 00:02:21,423
And we'll just mix it right on the brush.

62
00:02:22,402 --> 00:02:24,441
There we go, a little
thalo green and thalo blue.

63
00:02:24,442 --> 00:02:26,074
Okay, let's go back up here.

64
00:02:26,074 --> 00:02:27,894
I wanna have some water in this painting.

65
00:02:27,894 --> 00:02:29,173
I love water.

66
00:02:29,173 --> 00:02:31,734
And water is always level.

67
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:34,074
It's still water, it's always level.

68
00:02:34,074 --> 00:02:35,174
(scraping)

69
00:02:35,174 --> 00:02:37,014
So, just come across.

70
00:02:37,014 --> 00:02:38,354
Try to keep the strokes

71
00:02:38,354 --> 00:02:39,674
as straight as possible.

72
00:02:41,454 --> 00:02:42,953
Okay, now let's go to the other side,

73
00:02:42,953 --> 00:02:44,152
and pull this way.

74
00:02:44,152 --> 00:02:46,503
(scraping)

75
00:02:46,503 --> 00:02:49,074
Painting, see how the color's blending in.

76
00:02:49,074 --> 00:02:51,995
It's continually mixing
with the Magic White.

77
00:02:52,975 --> 00:02:54,776
Now, you could do all these
things on the palette,

78
00:02:54,776 --> 00:02:56,776
but they would take you a long time.

79
00:02:58,436 --> 00:03:00,515
Here we let it happen on
the, right on the canvas.

80
00:03:00,514 --> 00:03:03,135
(scraping)

81
00:03:03,135 --> 00:03:04,575
Mkay.

82
00:03:05,915 --> 00:03:07,034
Now, I'll wash the brush.

83
00:03:07,034 --> 00:03:10,055
And we wash our brushes
with odorless paint thinner.

84
00:03:10,055 --> 00:03:13,396
I never, never wash my
brushes with turpentine.

85
00:03:13,395 --> 00:03:16,214
Only with odorless paint thinner.

86
00:03:16,215 --> 00:03:18,015
(tapping)

87
00:03:18,014 --> 00:03:19,235
Shake off the excess.

88
00:03:19,235 --> 00:03:21,145
(banging)

89
00:03:21,635 --> 00:03:23,835
And, that's the most fun of all.

90
00:03:24,655 --> 00:03:26,115
Now, with a clean, dry brush,

91
00:03:26,115 --> 00:03:27,314
I'm gonna go back into the sky

92
00:03:27,314 --> 00:03:29,014
and just very quickly,

93
00:03:29,014 --> 00:03:30,715
blend it out a little bit.

94
00:03:30,716 --> 00:03:31,895
(fast scraping)

95
00:03:31,895 --> 00:03:33,665
Those light spots remain.

96
00:03:34,754 --> 00:03:35,573
There.

97
00:03:36,593 --> 00:03:38,183
Just let this happen.

98
00:03:38,495 --> 00:03:40,155
We really just sort of let it just flow

99
00:03:40,155 --> 00:03:41,794
right out of our mind,
right onto the canvas.

100
00:03:42,914 --> 00:03:44,574
And you don't have to spend a great deal

101
00:03:44,574 --> 00:03:45,894
of time planning and worrying.

102
00:03:45,895 --> 00:03:47,854
Just let it go. Let it go.

103
00:03:49,973 --> 00:03:50,715
Mkay.

104
00:03:50,715 --> 00:03:51,955
Tell you what, let's do.

