00:04:10,413 --> 00:04:11,954
Load a lot of paint into the bristles.

114
00:04:12,814 --> 00:04:14,034
Lot of paint.

115
00:04:14,034 --> 00:04:15,895
Kay, now let's go up to the canvas here.

116
00:04:15,895 --> 00:04:16,975
Maybe.

117
00:04:16,975 --> 00:04:18,655
Maybe, maybe, right here.

118
00:04:18,654 --> 00:04:20,653
Using just the corner of the brush.

119
00:04:20,653 --> 00:04:22,355
We'll put a happy little cloud.

120
00:04:23,115 --> 00:04:24,775
And clouds are very, very free.

121
00:04:25,894 --> 00:04:27,995
Very free, just let 'em
bounce around and play.

122
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:31,033
And we're looking for
areas here that are thick,

123
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:32,913
areas that are thin,
areas that have no paint.

124
00:04:33,903 --> 00:04:34,874
Keep the brush moving.

125
00:04:34,874 --> 00:04:35,955
Keep it moving.

126
00:04:35,954 --> 00:04:37,435
If you let it stay in one place,

127
00:04:37,435 --> 00:04:38,675
and keep doing this, you're gonna

128
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:42,130
you're gonna end up with a
big cotton ball up in the sky.

129
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:44,170
Let it move.

130
00:04:44,170 --> 00:04:45,990
(scratching)

131
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:49,050
I tell you what, let's go
over to the other side here.

132
00:04:49,050 --> 00:04:51,471
Maybe there's a happy little cloud that.

133
00:04:51,471 --> 00:04:52,910
Yeah, there was.

134
00:04:54,139 --> 00:04:55,390
He lives right there.

135
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,560
Just let him go.

136
00:04:59,901 --> 00:05:01,149
There he is.

137
00:05:01,149 --> 00:05:03,389
And you put these clouds
wherever you want 'em.

138
00:05:03,389 --> 00:05:05,689
This piece of canvas is your world.

139
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,189
It's your world.

140
00:05:10,778 --> 00:05:12,668
And you make your world
the way you want it.

141
00:05:15,478 --> 00:05:16,798
Now then, I'm gonna take

142
00:05:16,798 --> 00:05:19,347
a clean, dry, two and a half inch brush

143
00:05:19,348 --> 00:05:21,410
And I wanna blend, I want to blend

144
00:05:21,410 --> 00:05:22,830
the bottom of these clouds out

145
00:05:22,829 --> 00:05:24,389
without touching the top.

146
00:05:24,389 --> 00:05:26,209
So let's start right
here, and very lightly.

147
00:05:26,209 --> 00:05:28,288
Very lightly, very lightly.

148
00:05:29,348 --> 00:05:30,628
Three hairs and some air.

149
00:05:32,869 --> 00:05:34,886
Just let it caress the canvas.

150
00:05:35,636 --> 00:05:37,076
Barely, barely, barely touching.

151
00:05:37,076 --> 00:05:38,435
Blend the bottom out.

152
00:05:39,644 --> 00:05:40,955
Leave the top of the cloud alone.

153
00:05:40,956 --> 00:05:42,156
Kay, let's do this one.

154
00:05:42,156 --> 00:05:43,115
And work in layers.

155
00:05:43,115 --> 00:05:46,276
(scratching)

156
00:05:47,536 --> 00:05:49,478
Kay now, let's fluff this cloud.

157
00:05:49,478 --> 00:05:50,919
Now watch what happens.

158
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,300
We're gonna lift this cloud up.

159
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:53,639
And you're gonna pull little,

160
00:05:53,639 --> 00:05:55,359
little stringy things of paint up,

161
00:05:55,358 --> 00:05:57,318
don't worry about 'em,
don't worry about 'em.

162
00:05:58,468 --> 00:06:00,158
You want those to happen right now.

163
00:06:01,228 --> 00:06:03,519
And then very lightly, you just blend 'em,

164
00:06:03,519 --> 00:06:05,559
and it brings all of it together.

165
00:06:06,798 --> 00:06:08,878
Kay, let's do that again
over here on the other side.

166
00:06:09,658 --> 00:06:11,039
Just blend the bottom of the cloud out.

167
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,979
(scraping)

168
00:06:13,879 --> 00:06:15,059
Just like so.

169
00:06:15,059 --> 00:06:16,840
Fluff it up.

170
00:06:16,839 --> 00:06:18,979
And then blend it.

171
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:21,200
And this little son of a gun here,

172
00:06:21,199 --> 00:06:22,709
we don't want to forget him.

173
00:06:24,529 --> 00:06:26,159
And we'll just blend him out.

174
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,689
And fluff him up.

175
00:06:29,269 --> 00:06:31,058
And then very lightly,

176
00:06:31,059 --> 00:06:32,400
very lightly.

177
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:33,718
And that easy,

178
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:36,639
that easy, you've got some beautiful,

179
00:06:36,639 --> 00:06:38,360
beautiful, very effective little clouds.

180
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,038
Okay, I'll wash my brush.

181
00:06:41,038 --> 00:06:43,319
There's a screen in the bottom of this can

182
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,740
that I scrub the brush against.

183
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:46,278
It really helps.

184
00:06:47,396 --> 00:06:49,456
Helps get the paint out of the brush.

185
00:06:49,456 --> 00:06:53,477
I tell you what, my home
is in Fairbanks, Alaska,

186
00:06:53,476 --> 00:06:55,915
so I'm sort of hung up on mountains.

187
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:58,356
So let's build a fantastic
little mountain here.

188
00:06:59,776 --> 00:07:01,216
Go ahead and take some thalo blue,

189
00:07:02,396 --> 00:07:03,857
some Van Dyke Brown,

190
00:07:05,016 --> 00:07:08,276
and we'll use a little
bit alizarin crimson.

191
00:07:08,276 --> 00:07:10,757
So we have thalo blue, Van Dyke Brown,

192
00:07:10,757 --> 00:07:13,257
and a small amount of alizarin crimson.

193
00:07:15,086 --> 00:07:16,216
Now, the more crimson you put in,

194
00:07:16,216 --> 00:07:18,055
the more purplish your
mountain's gonna be.

195
00:07:18,055 --> 00:07:20,075
Pull this paint out very flat,

196
00:07:20,076 --> 00:07:23,576
and just cut across it so you
have a small roll of paint.

197
00:07:24,716 --> 00:07:26,375
There, right out on the edge of the knife.

198
00:07:27,406 --> 00:07:28,596
Let's go up here.

199
00:07:28,596 --> 00:07:31,716
Now, you have to make some
decisions in your world.

200
00:07:31,716 --> 00:07:33,515
Where's the mountain gonna live?

201
00:07:33,516 --> 00:07:35,855
I'm gonna have my
mountain live right there.

202
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:37,976
And you're really, really pushing

203
00:07:37,976 --> 00:07:39,635
this paint into the canvas.

204
00:07:40,696 --> 00:07:42,457
Really push it into the canvas.

205
00:07:44,706 --> 00:07:46,296
And anywhere you decide there's a bump

206
00:07:46,297 --> 00:07:47,737
or hill or big stone,

207
00:07:48,547 --> 00:07:49,727
put it in.

208
00:07:49,726 --> 00:07:50,975
Put it in.

209
00:07:50,975 --> 00:07:52,776
(short scraping)

210
00:07:52,776 --> 00:07:55,257
This is where ya exert your

211
00:07:56,365 --> 00:07:57,776
fantastic power

212
00:07:57,776 --> 00:07:58,836
is right here.

213
00:08:01,326 --> 00:08:02,246
Kay, now

214
00:08:02,245 --> 00:08:03,556
See you scrape off the excess paint.

215
00:08:03,557 --> 00:08:05,597
(scraping)

216
00:08:06,747 --> 00:08:09,747
And the canvas will keep what it wants.

217
00:08:10,997 --> 00:08:13,086
The value is in the material.

218
00:08:13,478 --> 00:08:14,958
Kay, now, I wanna remove more

219
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:16,198
excess paint and blend this out.

220
00:08:16,197 --> 00:08:17,536
Because the canvas is wet,

221
00:08:17,536 --> 00:08:19,996
this paint will move, it'll slide.

222
00:08:19,997 --> 00:08:21,516
You can move it all over the canvas.

223
00:08:22,786 --> 00:08:24,577
There we go, and just pull it out.

224
00:08:26,737 --> 00:08:28,197
And when you're painting mountains

225
00:08:28,197 --> 00:08:29,157
always remember

226
00:08:29,158 --> 00:08:30,658
if you can see the entire mountain

227
00:08:30,658 --> 00:08:33,358
it's always more distinct at the top

228
00:08:33,357 --> 00:08:34,977
than it is at the bottom.

229
00:08:36,158 --> 00:08:37,217
At the bottom of the mountain

230
00:08:37,217 --> 00:08:38,457
we have mist and

